txt.en: 'This is far enough. I will head back to camp from here.'
'Ha! That is it for the guards. Hurry before more show up!'
The Elf-scout Ianudirel has been trapped across the river from Krul Lugu. She must return to the near side, but expects to be ambushed when she attempts to cross the bridge.

'It was a pleasure fighting by your side, [placeholder]. I will be able to make it back to my brother's camp easily enough from here.\n\n'You should report to him as well. I am sure there is more to be done here.'
'Wait, something is wrong...they have found us! Fight through!'
Speak with Ianudirel and fight your way across the bridge to Krul Lugu.

'It was a pleasure fighting by your side, [placeholder]. I will be able to make it back to my brother's camp easily enough from here.\n\n'You should report to him as well. I am sure there is more to be done here.'

'Let us be off before the fell spirits find us!\n\n'Are you ready to go?'
'There are more of them rising from the mists ahead! We must not falter now!'
'There is no reason to wait about for them to find us. Let us be off!'
Reach the far side of the bridge with Ianudirel
'That is it! We have won through! Come on!'
